        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down</placeName>
                    <date>4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Angels!</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I can call you nothing else.—</p>
<p>I never dreamed of your taking so much trouble; the enumeration will be invaluable.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I will write this evening if possible &amp; explain what I have very little doubt is the case with Lythrum, &amp; which I am daily working to prove by most laborious crosses.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>But I write now to ask whether you will be more angelic than angels &amp; send me in tin, not tightly packed, with <hi rend="underline">little</hi> damp (<hi rend="underline">not wet</hi>) moss (perhaps tied round stems??) 2 or 3 flowers of <hi rend="underline">both</hi> forms of Hottonia: I much wish to measure pollen &amp; compare stigmas.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>GoodBye | My dear Angels | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

